# Student Theme Contrast

Custom per-student themes (`StudentTheme` in `src/lib/types.ts`) are AI- or
teacher-generated and are **not trusted** to have readable contrast. Every
place that consumes a student theme must run it through
`normalizeStudentTheme` from `@/lib/themeContrast` first.

## Rules

1. **Never read `student.theme.*` directly for rendering.** Compute an
   `activeTheme` once per component and read from that.

   ```tsx
   // ❌ BAD - unclamped AI colors
   <div style={{ color: student.theme?.text, background: student.theme?.background }} />

   // ✅ GOOD - WCAG-clamped at the boundary
   const activeTheme = normalizeStudentTheme(student.theme);
   <div style={activeTheme ? { color: 'var(--theme-text)', backgroundColor: 'var(--theme-bg)' } : undefined} />
   ```

2. **Don't mix global theme tokens with custom themes.** Inside a
   surface that uses `var(--theme-card)` / `var(--theme-bg)`, avoid
   `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-emerald-100`,
   `text-slate-800 dark:text-white`, hardcoded `text-white`, etc. —
   those resolve to the *global* palette and can be invisible on a
   themed background. Gate those classes behind `!activeTheme` and
   fall back to `var(--theme-text)` / neutral translucent colors when
   themed.

3. **For text on `--theme-primary` (buttons, badges), use
   `primaryForegroundFor(activeTheme)`** instead of hardcoded
   `text-white` or ad-hoc `getContrastColor` calls. Expose it as
   `--theme-primary-foreground` on the wrapper when multiple children
   need it.

4. **Persistence boundaries must normalize too.** Any code path that
   *saves* a `StudentTheme` (modals, API routes that return a theme)
   must run `normalizeStudentTheme` before `onSave` / the response, so
   bad palettes can't be stored in Firestore.

## When to skip normalization

- Non-color fields (`emoji`, `fontFamily`, `fontScale`) — the
  normalizer passes these through unchanged, so reading them from
  either `student.theme` or `activeTheme` is equivalent.
- Print sheets hard-coded to black-on-white (`PrizeRedeemTicketPrintSheet`,
  `Coupon` body) — those intentionally ignore the student theme.

## Tests

Contrast math + the normalizer are covered in
`src/lib/themeContrast.test.ts`. If you extend the normalizer, add a
test case there first.
